<div id="review_1373168241" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1373168241" />
    <a title="Calista" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16731747-calista"><img alt="Calista" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1436384393p2/16731747.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1373168241?book_show_action=true">Mar 12, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Calista" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Calista" href="/user/show/16731747-calista">Calista</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16731747-calista?shelf=award-various">award-various</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16731747-calista?shelf=bage-young-adult">bage-young-adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16731747-calista?shelf=favorite">favorite</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16731747-calista?shelf=genre-love-story">genre-love-story</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16731747-calista?shelf=diversity">diversity</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16731747-calista?shelf=2003">2003</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16731747-calista?shelf=lgbtq">lgbtq</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16731747-calista?shelf=z-david-levithan">z-david-levithan</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1373168241" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer554813372652406878">I love the innocence, purity and simplicity of the characters. I love that it isn&apos;t overly dramatic while it does have teen angst and drama in it. I enjoyed the range of characters and that the love triangle didn&apos;t really exist. Paul and Kyle were an old thing and I simply didn&apos;t feel much pull there. That was simply to complicate the plot. Paul and Noah are the new item. Noah moved to town and they are both openly gay. They both have a good life. <br/><br/>I love the character of Tony. He is gay and live</span>
  <span id="freeText554813372652406878" style="display:none">I love the innocence, purity and simplicity of the characters. I love that it isn't overly dramatic while it does have teen angst and drama in it. I enjoyed the range of characters and that the love triangle didn't really exist. Paul and Kyle were an old thing and I simply didn't feel much pull there. That was simply to complicate the plot. Paul and Noah are the new item. Noah moved to town and they are both openly gay. They both have a good life. <br /><br />I love the character of Tony. He is gay and lives in another town with conservative Christian parents who are against gays. Tony has it very difficult. I knew so many people growing up who had to deal with this. They were kicked out of their homes, disowned. This is the old archetype. I love the Story arch for Tony, I won't give that away here. David Levithan came up with such a beautiful ending for Tony. I simply love it and I wished we had thought of it as high schoolers back in the 90s. Tony has strength and bravery. He doesn't hate his parents. He tries to show who he is standing in his truth while being respectful. It is a beautiful depiction. <br /><br />Thank you Jesus for the book! I wish this and others like it were around during the 90s in small towns. There was Weetzie bat which I didn't hear of. The 80s and 90s was a dark time to be a high schooler who is LGBTQ. Teachers were gate keepers who kept out anyone not fitting into southern social norms. I am so glad the world is changing and growing up. I'm so glad boys can take boys to prom and girls can take girls to prom and kids can be who they are in more and more areas. This is positive and good. I am so happy that stories like this are possible and acceptance like this happens in places. I love to think that people can keep their innocence and have high school love. <br /><br />This book gave me life. I loved reading this and I loved thinking that Paul was a big idiot and Joni was such a bad friend. I rooted for the characters. I love that it gave us the nearly fairy tale ending and experience. I need that in a story along with other stories that aren't that. This book was beautiful and thank you so much David Levithan for writing this and giving it to the world. We need to know that this world is more than possible, it's here - not everywhere, but it's here.<br /><br />I hope that some day people simply won't care about anything but being a good person and living with love. Love is the goal. </span>
  <a data-text-id="554813372652406878" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


