<div id="review_1544479683" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1544479683" />
    <a title="Elle (ellexamines)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/52545435-elle-ellexamines"><img alt="Elle (ellexamines)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1624728854p2/52545435.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1544479683?book_show_action=true">Feb 10, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Elle (ellexamines)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Elle (ellexamines)" href="/user/show/52545435-elle-ellexamines">Elle (ellexamines)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52545435-elle-ellexamines?shelf=contemporary">contemporary</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52545435-elle-ellexamines?shelf=3-star">3-star</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52545435-elle-ellexamines?shelf=z-2015reads">z-2015reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52545435-elle-ellexamines?shelf=lgbtq">lgbtq</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1544479683" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14615557371198890241">This book is a bit of a period piece. It&apos;s a fantasy world for lgbt kids — escapism with a good message. In 2005, I can see this book having been a lighthouse for scared lgbt kids. Unfortunately, it really hasn&apos;t held up with the times. <br/><br/>Over time, I&apos;ve become less convinced of this world&apos;s relevancy, I suppose. When I reread this one in 2016, I felt like it was almost too much. And I don&apos;t mean “too much gay;” <b>it&apos;s depressing how this utopia isn&apos;t even close to a reality.</b> It&apos;s depressing that ha</span>
  <span id="freeText14615557371198890241" style="display:none">This book is a bit of a period piece. It's a fantasy world for lgbt kids — escapism with a good message. In 2005, I can see this book having been a lighthouse for scared lgbt kids. Unfortunately, it really hasn't held up with the times. <br /><br />Over time, I've become less convinced of this world's relevancy, I suppose. When I reread this one in 2016, I felt like it was almost too much. And I don't mean “too much gay;” <b>it's depressing how this utopia isn't even close to a reality.</b> It's depressing that having a trans girl as a cheerleader is unbelievable; it's depressing that accepting straight guy friends are rare. It's depressing how different this is from our reality. <b>It was a utopia to me last year, but now it's just a reminder of what isn't.</b><br /><br />As always, David Levithan's writing is <b>poetic</b> and gorgeous. His writing is probably the best thing about this book. Unfortunately, I don't feel it's quite as good here as in later books like <i>Two Boys Kissing</i>. <br /><br />Unfortunately, the slightly flat characters made it a less enjoyable experience. There's a romance here, but it's no different from any other. It feels as if Levithan didn't bother to build anything once he had his concept.<br /><br />It wasn't terrible, I enjoyed myself for sure, but I wouldn't bother. If you want to read Levithan, go with <i>Two Boys Kissing</i>. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14615557371198890241" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


